5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69207eb2e1a9cbb014deb449%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221432%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPauline%20Pusser's%20grave%20was%20exhumed%20in%202024%20as%20part%20of%20the%20TBI's%20investigation.%3Cp%3EMcNairy%20County%20Archives%2FTennessee%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%2C%20it%20was%20a%20seminal%20moment%20in%20a%20Southern%20tale%20that%20has%20been%20handed%20down%20through%20generations.%20Could%20it%20all%20have%20been%20a%20lie%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20wouldn't%20come%20for%20another%20year%20and%20a%20half%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20it%20did%2C%20it%20would%20shatter%20a%20legend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20you%20see%20when%20driving%20into%20town%20is%20a%20massive%20sign%3A%20%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20Adamsville%3A%20Home%20of%20Sheriff%20Buford%20Pusser.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20to%20town%20in%20March%2C%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20buzz%20that%20the%20Tennessee%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation's%20findings%20would%20soon%20be%20revealed.%20The%20soil%20at%20Pauline's%20gravesite%20was%20still%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20had%20been%20no%20autopsy%20performed%20in%201967%2C%20one%20reason%20some%20in%20McNairy%20County%20question%20whether%20that%20night%20went%20down%20exactly%20as%20Buford%20described.%20It's%20also%20why%20the%20TBI%20took%20another%20look%20at%20Pauline's%20cold%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20in%20town%20stand%20by%20the%20Buford%20legend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20garbage%20out%20there%20written.%20It%20needs%20to%20be%20piled%20up%20and%20burned%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Sweat%2C%2070%2C%20told%20me%20from%20his%20body%20shop%20just%20outside%20Adamsville.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Sweat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920bc66e1a9cbb014debf35%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteve%20Sweat%2C%20a%20self-described%20Pusser%20historian%2C%20drives%20a%20replica%20of%20the%20patrol%20car%20from%20the%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20movie%20every%20Memorial%20Day%20during%20the%20Buford%20Pusser%20festival.%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESweat%20has%20lived%20his%20entire%20life%20in%20McNairy%20County%20and%20considers%20himself%20a%20historian%20on%20all%20things%20Pusser.%20His%20shop%20is%20home%20to%20a%20collection%20of%20photographs%20and%20memorabilia%20that%20he%20has%20compiled%20over%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Buford%20busted%20Sweat's%20older%20brother's%20moonshine%20still%20in%201963%2C%20he's%20been%20fascinated%20by%20the%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%206%20or%207%20years%20old%20and%20would%20see%20this%20young%20chief%20of%20police%2C%206-foot-6%20with%20a%20flattop%20haircut%2C%20all%20over%20town.%20There%20was%20a%20picture%20of%20him%20in%20the%20paper%20every%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Sweat%20said%2C%20pausing%20for%20a%20moment%20as%20he%20choked%20up.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20bigger%20than%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESweat%20used%20to%20lead%20tours%20of%20key%20Pusser%20sites%20around%20town.%20Every%20Memorial%20Day%20during%20the%20Buford%20Pusser%20Festival%2C%20he%20drives%20a%20replica%20of%20the%20patrol%20car%20Joe%20Don%20Baker%20drove%20when%20he%20portrayed%20the%20sheriff%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rottentomatoes.com%2Fm%2F1023007-walking_tall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1973%20movie%2C%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETina%20Mullis%2C%2060%2C%20called%20the%20TBI%20investigation%20%26quot%3Bjust%20silly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20are%20they%20going%20to%20prove%20something%2057%20years%20later%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMullis%2C%20a%20distant%20relative%20of%20Pusser%2C%20is%20the%20curator%20of%20Adamsville's%20Buford%20Pusser%20Home%20%26amp%3B%20Museum.%20Tucked%20away%20in%20a%20quiet%20neighborhood%20next%20to%20a%20baseball%20field%20on%20Pusser%20Street%2C%20the%20modest%20ranch%20home%20is%20a%20destination%20for%20travel%20vloggers%2C%20true%20crime%20fans%2C%20and%20awe-struck%20law%20enforcement%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tina%20Mullis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69207ffb89026fbb4d0e2510%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETina%20Mullis%2C%20the%20curator%20of%20the%20Buford%20Pusser%20Home%20%26amp%3B%20Museum%2C%20called%20the%20TBI%20investigation%20%26quot%3Bjust%20silly.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMullis%20sits%20me%20down%20in%20Buford%20and%20Pauline's%20living%20room%20to%20play%20me%20a%20video%20titled%20%26quot%3BLiars%20%26amp%3B%20Legends%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20eight-minute%20history%20of%20the%20sheriff%20and%20his%20battles%20with%20the%20State%20Line%20Mob.%20She%20walks%20me%20through%20the%20home%2C%20lined%20with%20memorabilia%20and%20newspaper%20clippings%20of%20Pusser's%20moonshine%20busts%2C%20and%20points%20out%20a%20carefully%20preserved%20bedroom%20she%20says%20Elvis%20stayed%20in%20on%20the%20day%20of%20Buford's%20funeral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuford%20died%20seven%20years%20after%20Pauline%20in%20a%20fiery%20car%20wreck%20on%20Highway%2064.%20Eyewitnesses%20told%20law%20enforcement%20at%20the%20time%20they%20saw%20him%20driving%20at%20a%20high%20speed%20before%20the%20crash%3B%20others%20said%20they%20smelled%20alcohol%20on%20his%20breath%20before%20he%20got%20behind%20the%20wheel.%20The%20charred%20remains%20of%20his%201974%20Corvette%20sit%20on%20display%20in%20the%20museum's%20garage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20through%20the%20museum%20is%20akin%20to%20visiting%20Graceland%20with%20a%20dash%20of%20Ripley's%20Believe%20It%20or%20Not!%20I'm%20filled%20with%20fascination%2C%20but%20also%20skeptical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Buford%20Pusser%20Home%20%26amp%3B%20Museum%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F692080b2abd5e944effb3acb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBuford%20Pusser's%20home%20has%20been%20preserved%20to%20look%20as%20it%20did%20when%20he%20lived%20there.%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20McNairy%20County%20sheriff%2C%20Guy%20Buck%2C%2058%2C%20who%20has%20held%20the%20post%20for%2015%20years%2C%20described%20Pusser's%20appeal%20thusly%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20time%20before%20the%20internet%20and%20cable%20TV%2C%20he%20was%20a%20world-class%20promoter.%20Whether%20his%20stories%20were%20true%20or%20not%2C%20people%20ran%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPusser%20was%20a%20master%20of%20self-promotion.%20He%20got%20his%20start%20as%20a%20professional%20wrestler%2C%20%26quot%3BBuford%20the%20Bull%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20the%201950s%20in%20Chicago%2C%20where%20he%20met%20Pauline%2C%20a%20divorc%C3%A9e%20with%20two%20kids.%20They%20married%20in%201959%2C%20had%20a%20child%2C%20and%20in%201962%20moved%20back%20to%20Adamsville%2C%20where%20he%20succeeded%20his%20father%20as%20chief%20of%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Buford%20Pusser%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920812be1a9cbb014deb4e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221064%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBuford%20Pusser%20became%20famous%20throughout%20the%20South%20in%20the%201960s%20for%20busting%20moonshine%20stills%20and%20battling%20the%20State%20Line%20Mob.%3Cp%3EMcNairy%20County%20Archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPusser%20quickly%20began%20busting%20moonshine%20stills%2C%20and%20at%2026%2C%20he%20was%20elected%20sheriff%20%E2%80%94%20a%20position%20he%20helped%20secure%20thanks%20to%20the%20media%20coverage%20of%20his%20exploits%2C%20which%20he%20had%20organized%20as%20press%20officer.%20Pusser%20broke%20up%20over%20140%20stills%20in%20his%20career%2C%20according%20to%20the%20museum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%201967%20shooting%2C%20Pusser's%20lore%20grew.%20In%201971%2C%20W.R.%20Morris%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Twelfth%20of%20August%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20introduced%20people%20outside%20the%20Southeast%20to%20him%20and%20his%20battles%20with%20the%20State%20Line%20Mob.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D3hd6Ve6mNaw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEddie%20Bond%20released%20the%20song%20%26quot%3BLegend%20of%20Buford%20Pusser%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20twangy%20tune%20that%20played%20throughout%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20attention%20found%20its%20way%20to%20Hollywood%20and%20crooner%20Bing%20Crosby%2C%20whose%20production%20company%20bought%20Pusser's%20life%20rights%20for%20%2410%2C000%20and%20made%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall.%26quot%3B%20The%20filmmakers%20ran%20with%20backwoods%20stories%20that%20Pusser%20once%20raided%20a%20moonshine%20still%20with%20just%20a%20fence%20pole.%20(Sheriff%20Buck%20debunks%20that%20myth%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20farthest%20thing%20from%20the%20truth.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20movie%20poster.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920816089026fbb4d0e2572%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBuford%20Pusser's%20story%20inspired%20the%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20movie%20franchise%20and%20a%20TV%20series.%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20era%20of%20vigilante%20blockbusters%20like%20%26quot%3BDirty%20Harry%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BBilly%20Jack%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20earned%20%2440%20million%20on%20a%20%24500%2C000%20budget.%20Variety%20reported%20that%20in%20some%20regions%20of%20the%20South%2C%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20did%20better%20than%20%26quot%3BThe%20Godfather.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20stepping%20down%20as%20sheriff%20in%201970%2C%20Pusser%20hobnobbed%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20Johnny%20Cash%20and%20Dolly%20Parton%2C%20made%20money%20off%20speaking%20tours%2C%20and%20entertained%20the%20idea%20of%20running%20for%20governor.%20In%201974%2C%20he%20attended%20the%20press%20conference%20where%20it%20was%20announced%20he%20would%20play%20himself%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20sequel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20he%20died%20in%20a%20car%20wreck%20at%2036.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pusser%20franchise%20lived%20on%3A%20Actor%20Bo%20Svenson%20took%20over%20the%20role%2C%20starring%20in%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%20Part%202%26quot%3B%20(1975)%20and%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%3A%20Final%20Chapter%26quot%3B%20(1977)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20short-lived%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20TV%20series%20(1981).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20that%20followed%2C%20Pusser's%20daughter%2C%20Dwana%2C%20built%20her%20father's%20myth%20into%20a%20business.%20She%20sold%20her%20parents'%20house%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Tennessee%20in%201987%20for%20Adamsville%20to%20use%20as%20a%20for-profit%20museum%20and%20helped%20turn%20the%20jailhouse%20in%20nearby%20Selmer%2C%20where%20Pusser%20had%20his%20office%2C%20into%20a%20tourist%20attraction.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdwayne-the-rock-johnson-movies-ranked%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDwayne%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rock%26quot%3B%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%20starred%20in%20the%202004%20remake%20of%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%2C%26quot%3B%20Dwana%20posed%20for%20press%20photos%20with%20him.%20(Dwana%20died%20in%202018.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dwana%20Pusser%20and%20Dwayne%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rock%26quot%3B%20Johnson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F692081c3e1a9cbb014deb509%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222157%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDwayne%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rock%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20with%20Dwana%20Pusser%20promoting%20the%202004%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20remake%20at%20the%20Pusser%20Museum.%3Cp%3ER.%20Diamond%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20years%20passed%2C%20whispers%20about%20the%201967%20shooting%20spread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESvenson%20told%20me%20that%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20he%20was%20approached%20by%20people%20who%20told%20him%20that%20Buford's%20gunshot%20wound%20was%20self-inflicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20even%20saw%20photos%20of%20Buford%20on%20the%20operating%20table%2C%20photos%20that%20showed%20powder%20burn%20on%20his%20face%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20whatever%20gun%20was%20used%20was%20held%20very%20close%20to%20his%20head%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%20didn't%20align%20with%20the%20sheriff's%20story%2C%20the%20actor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20making%20the%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20sequels%2C%20did%20Svenson%20think%20Pusser%20could%20have%20killed%20his%20wife%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20sometimes%20public%20people%20have%20skeletons%20in%20their%20closets%2C%26quot%3B%20Svenson%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20what%20he%20represented%20I%20felt%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20was%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F5Trrb%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Timeline%20of%20events%20surrounding%20Pauline%20Pusser's%20murder%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F5Trrb%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20Hathcock's%20family%20name%20has%20been%20intertwined%20with%20Pusser's%20mythology%20for%20most%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20aunt%2C%20Louise%20Hathcock%2C%20ran%20the%20Shamrock%20Motel%2C%20a%20restaurant%20and%20motel%20known%20for%20bootlegging%2C%20gambling%2C%20and%20nightly%20fights.%20In%20February%201966%2C%20Sheriff%20Pusser%20arrived%20to%20question%20Louise%20about%20two%20patrons%20who%20accused%20her%20of%20stealing.%20The%20two%20were%20speaking%20in%20a%20back%20room%20when%2C%20according%20to%20Pusser%2C%20Louise%20pulled%20out%20a%20gun%20and%20shot%20at%20him.%20She%20missed%2C%20and%20Pusser%20said%20he%20shot%20and%20killed%20Louise%20in%20self-defense.%20A%20grand%20jury%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20faceoff%20would%20cement%20the%20Pusser%20vs.%20State%20Line%20Mob%20lore%20that%20would%20be%20reported%20in%20newspapers%20and%20chronicled%20in%20Morris'%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Twelfth%20of%20August.%26quot%3B%20A%20character%20bearing%20a%20strong%20resemblance%20to%20Louise%20Hathcock%20was%20later%20made%20the%20main%20villain%20in%20the%20first%20%26quot%3BWalking%20Tall%26quot%3B%20movie%3A%20Callie%20Hacker%2C%20a%20madam%20who%20ran%20a%20moonshine%2C%20gambling%2C%20and%20prostitution%20operation%20out%20of%20her%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20Hathcock%2C%2075%2C%20claims%20Pusser%20killed%20his%20aunt%20in%20cold%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225952%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dennis%20Hathcock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920838ee1a9cbb014deb585%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223968%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDennis%20Hathcock's%20aunt%20Louise%20was%20killed%20by%20Pusser%20in%20the%201960s%20in%20a%20standoff%20at%20the%20Shamrock%20Motel%2C%20which%20once%20stood%20here.%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20family%20has%20borne%20the%20brunt%20of%20many%20lies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20his%20own%20run-ins%20with%20Pusser.%20Hathcock%20was%2016%20the%20night%20of%20August%2011%2C%201967%2C%20when%20he%20and%20a%20friend%20were%20riding%20around%20on%20Hathcock's%20CB450%20Honda%20motorcycle.%20After%20playing%20some%20pool%20in%20Selmer%2C%20they%20got%20bored%20and%20decided%20to%20do%20what%20they%20always%20did%3A%20tail%20Pusser%20while%20he%20patrolled%20the%20county.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHathcock%20said%20he%20knew%20a%20girl%20Pusser%20was%20seeing%20on%20the%20side%2C%20Ann%20Henderson.%20They%20found%20him%20banging%20on%20the%20door%20of%20her%20friend's%20house%2C%20yelling%20for%20Henderson%20to%20come%20out.%20After%20he%20and%20Henderson%20were%20done%20talking%2C%20Hathcock%20heard%20Pusser%20yell%20out%20after%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20be%20putting%20flowers%20on%20my%20grave%20tomorrow!%26quot%3B%20(Henderson%20confirmed%20this%20in%20her%20interview%20with%20the%20TBI.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHathcock%20said%20they%20stopped%20following%20Pusser%20around%202%3A30%20a.m.%20on%20the%2012th.%20When%20he%20heard%20about%20the%20shooting%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20Hathcock%20raced%20to%20New%20Hope%20Road%2C%20where%20a%20police%20officer%20told%20him%20to%20leave.%20Hathcock%20left%20and%20passed%20the%20second%20ambush%20site%2C%20which%20was%20littered%20with%20shell%20casings.%20He%20said%20he%20saw%20bloody%20remains%20of%20what%20looked%20like%20a%20scalp%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road%20and%20went%20back%20to%20the%20officer%20to%20show%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22859%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Archival%20image%20of%20the%20ambush%20site%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69208466e1a9cbb014deb5ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22638%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDennis%20Hathcock%20and%20a%20friend%20photographed%20talking%20to%20authorities%20at%20the%20shooting%20site%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20August%2012%2C%201967.%3Cp%3EMcNairy%20County%20Archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20when%20Hathcock%20read%20news%20reports%20where%20Buford%20described%20how%20Pauline%20was%20killed%2C%20he%20felt%20a%20pit%20in%20his%20stomach.%20Something%20wasn't%20right.%20He%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20the%20FBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20afraid%20to%20go%20to%20the%20TBI%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Hathcock%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20knew%20they%20were%20overlooking%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHathcock%20said%20he%20didn't%20get%20a%20better%20reception%20at%20the%20FBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20laughed%20me%20out%20of%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Hathcock%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BThey%20just%20made%20fun%20of%20me%2C%20that%20Pusser%20would%20be%20involved%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Elam%20knows%20how%20hard%20it%20is%20to%20find%20the%20shooting%20site%20on%20New%20Hope%20Road%2C%20so%20he%20offered%20to%20drive%20me%20there%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20exact%20route%20Buford%20drove%20with%20Pauline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mike%20Elam%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920bce3e1a9cbb014debf4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMike%20Elam%2C%20pictured%20here%20at%20the%20shooting%20site%2C%20went%20from%20Pusser%20believer%20to%20the%20sheriff's%20biggest%20critic.%3Cp%3ERay%20Di%20Pietro%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20chatting%20with%20Elam's%20wife%2C%20Connie%2C%20who's%20sitting%20in%20the%20back%20seat%2C%20when%20Elam%20pulls%20over%20and%20begins%20digging%20under%20his%20seat.%20Suddenly%2C%20he%20pulls%20out%20a%20handgun%20and%20swiftly%20holsters%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20kidding%20when%20I%2